(MS-IS) or Library Science (MS-LS) Apply The master's degree is offered in a residential format in Denton, in an off-campus format in Houston, and through the department's online program. The master's program prepares information professionals for work in a variety of roles and application settings, including various information agencies and all types of libraries. In addition, the program prepares at a master's level individuals who wish to pursue study in the theoretical development of information science. Interdisciplinary Information Science PhD Program (IIS PhD) Apply The University of North Texas Interdisciplinary Information Science PhD Program (IIS PhD Program) responds to the varied and changing needs of an information age, and to the increasing recognition of the central role of information and information technologies in individual, social, economic and cultural affairs. Graduates of the program are prepared to contribute to the advancement and evolution of the information society in a variety of roles and settings as administrators, researchers and educators. Certificate Programs The department also offers certificate (non-degree) programs. Certificates of Advanced Study are offered in Health Informatics and Rural Library Management. Graduate Academic Certificates are offered in the following areas: Advanced Management in Libraries & Information Agencies, Archival Management, Digital Content Management, Digital Curation and Data Management, Leadership in Professional Development in Technology for Schools, Rural Library Management, Storytelling  and Youth Services in Libraries and Information Settings.   Advisors Degree Programs  Bachelor of Science Master of Science Interdisciplinary IS PhD  Certificate Programs  School Library Certification Graduate Academic Certificates Certificates of Advanced Study  Cohorts Onsite Institute     Top                          Main Menu Home About Us People Programs Students Financial Assistance Research Alumni  Universi